RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in darts.

RIOS.name: Manoa Debate Union at UHM
RIOS.description: The Mānoa Debate Union serves not only the students of the University but also the state of Hawai‘i at large. An internationally competitive debate program brings honor and esteem to the University of Hawai‘i, attracting the best and brightest students and encouraging the top talent from our Hawai‘i secondary schools to remain in the islands for higher education. Currently, we lose many articulate, future leaders to mainland schools with well-endowed debate programs. By offering an alternative close to home, we create a pipeline for talent. An intramural collegiate debate league exposes students to a diversity of ideas and improves discourse between institutions of higher learning within our state. Finally, our service dedicated to fostering the forensic development of Hawai‘i youth helps establish a clear path between organizations like the Hawai‘i Speech League and the University of Hawai‘i. By providing resources for development to youth, we empower them to be leaders and agents of change in their communities, and in so doing, we improve the governance of our state.

RIOS.name: Manoa Improv Players
RIOS.description: UHM improv theater club.

RIOS.name: Manoa Peer Advisor Program
RIOS.description: MPA Strives to provide the University of Hawai`i at Mānoa student body with available and resourceful Peer Advisors who will guide the students through all stages in their college careers.

RIOS.name: Manoa Pre-Law Association
RIOS.description: The Manoa Pre-Law Association is excited to start the new semester and hopefully make it a memorable one for you.

RIOS.name: Manoa Sophomore Experience
RIOS.description: The mission of the MSE is to help rising sophomores and sophomores navigate academic requirements and campus life so they become engaged with the campus community and invested in their college experience. Students will utilize resources relevant to academic requirements, post-graduation goals, and campus life.

RIOS.name: Manoa Ultimate Disc
RIOS.description: UHM ultimate frisbee club.

RIOS.name: Marine Robotics at University of Hawaii
RIOS.description: Marine Robotics at the University of Hawai`i (MRUH) is an organization that serves as a vehicle through which students can learn about and participate in autonomous marine robotics.

RIOS.name: Master of Education in Teaching Student Organization
RIOS.description: UHM club for people in the Master of Education in Teaching.

RIOS.name: Medical Education Student Interest Group
RIOS.description: UHM RIO club for medical education students.

RIOS.name: Medical Innovation and Design Hawaii
RIOS.description: MIND Hawaii is a program associated with the University of Hawaii whose mission is to bring together students and faculty from various fields such as Business, Medicine, Engineering, Law, and Marketing to develop solutions to challenging medical problems. MIND Hawaii provides education, mentorship, and networking opportunities. The program culminates in a year-end competition for additional funding to support the next step in the innovation lifecycle.

RIOS.name: Medical Students for Choice
RIOS.description: We believe that all people should have access to health services that allow them to lead safe, healthy lives including all aspects of sexual and reproductive health consistent with their own personal and cultural values.

RIOS.name: Medical Student Mentorship Program
RIOS.description: Founded in 2002, the Medical Student Mentorship Program (MSMP) is a student-run organization that pairs current medical students John A. Burns School of Medicine with undergraduate students interested in pursuing a career in medicine. Through these pairings, our goal is to help foster relationships between undergraduates and medical students and faculty. Over the years, we have paired more than 600 mentees with medical student mentors via an extensive matching process. Mentor-mentee pairs contact each other regularly and participate in a variety of activities throughout the year.

RIOS.name: Medical Students of the Class of 2022 at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for the class of 2022 at JABSOM.

RIOS.name: Micronesia Connections at UH Manoa
RIOS.description: The Micronesia Connections Club at UH-Manoa is a collective group of students that come from different parts of the region.

RIOS.name: MILUN
RIOS.description: Milun is a local organization focused on promoting South Asian culture.

RIOS.name: Mortar Board Senior National Honor Society (Hui Po'okela Chapter)
RIOS.description: Mortar Board Senior National Honor Society is one of the oldest organizations at the University of Hawai'i at Mānoa. It has long been recognized throughout the campus and O'ahu community for its continued partnership with diverse service projects with other student clubs and non-profit organizations all over the island. This is a national collegiate honor society for students in their senior year.  Each chapter is typically comprised of only a handful of carefully selected applicants for the year - the Hui Po'okela Chapter usually does not exceed 25 members at a time. Potential members are chosen based on how they measure in accord with Mortar Board's key values: scholarship, leadership, and service. Those who excel in said values are then carefully examined through a series of interviews hosted by the chapter's current members. Once in Mortar Board, you will engage in various community service and fundraising activities.  It is a great opportunity to give back to the community and form close friendships with your fellow Mortar Board members.

RIOS.name: N? Hawai'i 'Imi Loa Hui Haum?na
RIOS.description: The mission of Nā Hawai‘i ‘Imi Loa is to service the Hawaiian community, by strengthening the Native Hawaiian presence in the Library and Information Sciences profession, and by building the capacity of the Hawaiian community in Library and Information Sciences practices.

RIOS.name: Na Koa
RIOS.description: We are simply a group of imperfect people striving to love God and live like Jesus. As diverse as our congregation is, the Word reminds us that we are one body (Romans 12:4-5, 1 Corinthians 12:12). In such a divided world, we aim to be united in the Spirit (Ephesians 4:3-6). God loves you, and we want to do everything we can to remind each other of that daily.

RIOS.name: Na Koa Lani Booster Club
RIOS.description: The Na Koa Lani Booster Club is a university organization whose purpose is to bolster the development of future Air Force leaders by supporting and improving their college experience through sponsored extracurricular activities. Events such as Dining Out, Dining In, and Wing Socials are all sponsored by the Na Koa Lani Booster Club.  The Na Koa Lani Booster Club promotes comaraderie in the pursuit of bringing communities together.

RIOS.name: Narrative Medicine Interest Group
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in narrative medicine.

RIOS.name: National Panhellenic Conferene
RIOS.description: We, as undergraduate members of women's fraternities, stand for good scholarship, for guarding of good health, for maintenance of fine standards, and for serving, to the best of our ability, our college community. Cooperation for furthering fraternity life, in harmony with its best possibilities, is the ideal that shall guide our fraternity activities. We, as fraternity women, stand for service through the development of character inspired by the close contact and deep friendship of individual fraternity and Panhellenic life. The opportunity for wide and wise human service, through mutual respect and helpfulness, is the tenet by which we strive to live.

RIOS.name: Natural Sciences Student Ambassadors
RIOS.description: Aloha! The UH Manoa Student Academic Success Center offers advising services for prospective, incoming, and current students majoring in the Natural Sciences.

RIOS.name: OB/GYN Interest Group
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in OB/GYN.

RIOS.name: Oncology Interest Group at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in oncology.

RIOS.name: Opthalmology Interest Group
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in opathalmology.

RIOS.name: Pacific Asia Travel Association
RIOS.description: The Pacific Asia Travel Association (PATA) is a membership association acting as a catalyst for the responsible development of the Asia Pacific travel and tourism industry.

RIOS.name: Pacific Asian Legal Student Organization
RIOS.description: PALSO regularly welcomes attorneys and academics for talks and lectures on a range of topics and hosts a number of social events that gathers the law school community to promote our common interests in Pacific and Asian cultures.

RIOS.name: Partners in Health Engage UH Manoa Chapter
RIOS.description: PIH Engage is a grassroots network of volunteer community organizers that aims to build and advance the right to health movement by growing and amplifying PIH’s work. We bring resources and build power to stabilize the financing of health care systems globally by raising funds and engaging with policy makers. We focus all of our actions on the 3 pillars: Fundraising, Advocacy, and Community Building.

RIOS.name: Partnership for Social Justice at JABSOM
RIOS.description: A multi-disciplinary coalition of professional and graduate school in the University of Hawaii system and other private colleges.

RIOS.name: Patient Safety and Quality Improvement Interest Group
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in Patient Safety and Quality Improvement.

RIOS.name: Pediatric Interest Group at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for students at the JABSOM interested in pediatric.

RIOS.name: Peer Mentor Ohana
RIOS.description: Peer Mentor Ohana (PMO) is a registered independent organization (RIO) based out of the Learning Assistance Center in Sinclair Library. We're students passionate about making a difference on campus by providing peer academic assistance to our fellow students at the University of Hawai'i at Manoa.

RIOS.name: Peer Mentoring Program at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for peer mentor at JABSOM.

RIOS.name: Phi Alpha Nu Sigma Honor Society
RIOS.description: The purpose of Phi Alpha Honor Society is to provide a closer bond among students of social work and promote humanitarian goals and ideas. Phi Alpha fosters high standards of education for social workers and invites into membership those who have attained excellence in scholarship and achievement in social work.

RIOS.name: Phi Alpha Theta (Alpha Beta Epsilon)
RIOS.description: Phi Alpha Theta is an American honor society for undergraduate and graduate students and professors of history.

RIOS.name: Phi Mu
RIOS.description: Welcome to the Iota Alpha chapter of Phi Mu! We are an organization that provides personal and academic development, service to others, commitment to excellence and lifelong friendships through a shared tradition. Phi Mu was founded in 1852 at Wesleyan College in Macon, Georgia, making it the second oldest sorority in the country. Our chapter at UH Manoa was founded in 2015, since then our sisterhood bond continues to grow as we share countless traditions and memories together. Phi Mu is our hΦΜe away from home and we invite you to discover our sisterhood through our website, happy exploring!

RIOS.name: Philippine Medical Student Association of Hawaii
RIOS.description: Since its founding in 1978, PMAH has been at the forefront of servicing the medical needs of Hawaii’s community-at-large. Hawaii is replete with Filipino-American doctors and even non-Filipino doctors who serve the Filipino community. As such, we invite you to become part of our ohana (family). With its three affiliates, PMAH gives you several opportunities to make a difference in our community and beyond.

RIOS.name: Pi Gamma Mu
RIOS.description: Pi Gamma Mu is the oldest and preeminent honor society in the social sciences. Its mission is to encourage and recognize superior scholarship in social science disciplines and to foster cooperation and social service among its members. Pi Gamma Mu serves the various social science disciplines which seek to understand and explain human behavior and social relationships as well as their related problems and issues.

RIOS.name: Pi Sigma Alpha- Tau Pi Chapter
RIOS.description: The University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa is home to the Tau Pi Chapter of Pi Sigma Alpha, the National Political Science Honor Society. Membership is open to undergraduate juniors and seniors interested in Political Science and graduate students pursuing a degree in Political Science.

RIOS.name: Pi Tau Sigma
RIOS.description: Pi Tau Sigma is the National Honorary Mechanical Engineering Fraternity and is a member of the Association of College Honor Societies. With 159 chapters installed over the past century, all but two currently maintain active status. There are chapters located at universities in almost every state in the United States with new chapters being established regularly. The society has also gone international, establishing chapters in Qatar and Mexico.

RIOS.name: Political Science Club at UH
RIOS.description: UHM club for student interested in the political science degrees.

RIOS.name: Powerlifting Club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
RIOS.description: Powerlifting Club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa is a educational organization focused on student services. Founded in 2019, Powerlifting Club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa is headquartered in Honolulu, HI.

RIOS.name: Pre-Medical Association
RIOS.description: THE PRE-MEDICAL ASSOCIATION (PMA) IS THE LARGEST PRE-HEALTH ORGANIZATION AT THE UNIVERSITY OF HAWAI’I AT MĀNOA. PMA STRIVES TO PROVIDE STUDENTS WITH A HOLISTIC PERSPECTIVE OF THE FIELD OF HEALTHCARE, HELP MEMBERS TO DEVELOP ACADEMICALLY AND PROFESSIONALLY THROUGH SERVICE AND LEADERSHIP OPPORTUNITIES, AND FOSTER COLLEGIALITY AMONG PEERS WITH SIMILAR GOALS AND INTERESTS.

RIOS.name: Pre-Phamarcy Association at UH Manoa
RIOS.description: The Pre-Pharmacy Association at the University of Manoa is run entirely by students. We network with fellow students who share the same goal of one day becoming certified pharmacists. Together, we share experiences, grow, and learn.

RIOS.name: Primary Care Progress at University of Hawaii
RIOS.description: Founded in 2010, Primary Care Progress is a national organization committed to strengthening the people at the heart of care through leadership development and community building.  Growing out of a grassroots primary care revitalization effort launched at Harvard Medical School, PCP has transformed over the years from an alliance of medical school-based teams promoting primary care, into a national movement — a powerful learning collaborative of current and future healthcare professionals from across disciplines and career stages.  So whether you’re an executive leadership team navigating change, a clinician implementing new team-based models, or a health system catalyzing action on community health, we’re here to help you and your teams thrive.

RIOS.name: Protection of Ocean and Nature Organization
RIOS.description: Formed in the Spring of 2017, PONO is a professional volunteer group that seeks to take real action through language analysis skills. Language is all around us, and PONO is dedicated to closely inspecting what reality is constructed from that language.

RIOS.name: Psi SIgma: The Psychology Connection
RIOS.description: Psi Sigma: The Psychology Connection is the first social club for psychology majors at the University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa. Psi Sigma was created by Victoria Chang in September 2014. We encourage the pursuit of psychological science, foster enduring connections among peers in psychology, and advance the academic and professional development of our members.  Psi Sigma upholds the values of knowledge, benevolence, and integrity.

RIOS.name: Public Administration Student Organization
RIOS.description: Our mission is is to foster educational collaboration and networking among members, to provide a platform for the exchange of ideas, and to build professional relationships with the public service community in Hawai‘i.

RIOS.name: Public Relations Student Society of America
RIOS.description: Our student organization is here to help YOU, the student, achieve success in your post-college career life. It all starts now, while you're still in college, but don't sweat it! There are no major commitments for you to sign up for, and it's entirely up to you how much you want to participate in our our free activities and events!

RIOS.name: Rainbow Jugglers Juggling Club
RIOS.description: Founded by former student Tricia Adams in 1989, the RIO aims to show the fun and concentration of juggling.

RIOS.name: Regent and Presidential Scholars Club
RIOS.description: The UH Board of Regents established the Regents and Presidential Scholarships to support students with a record of outstanding academic achievement.

RIOS.name: Reformed University Fellowship
RIOS.description: RUF is a Christian fellowship on over 150 college campuses across the country. Why do we exist? Many religions and philosophies exist to point us onto a path to find God, enlightenment, or the good life. As Christians we believe the opposite. God came to us—in Jesus Christ. We gather together to study the Bible so that we might not only know about Him, but know Him personally. We are here for the “convinced” and the “unconvinced,” the lost, the found, the burned, bored, cynical, and spiritual. None of us has it all together, but we are deeply committed to the gospel of Jesus, believing it has the power to change any person, any community, any culture.

RIOS.name: Rural Health Interest Group at JABSOM
RIOS.description: The Global & Rural Health Interest Group at JABSOM seeks to promote interest & awareness in prominent global & rural health issues!

RIOS.name: S-cubed
RIOS.description: S-Cubed (the SSS Registered Independent Organization) offers many social and community service events during the year.

RIOS.name: Salsa Dancing @ UHM
RIOS.description: A club about Salsa Dancing

RIOS.name: Science Communicators Ohana
RIOS.description: We are a collective of scientists and science enthusiasts with the desire to communicate our science effectively. As part of the Science Communicators ‘Ohana (SciComm ‘Ohana), a Registered Independent Organization at the University of Hawai’i at Mānoa, we get together to practice talking about our science to audiences not in our field.

RIOS.name: Second Language Studies Student Association
RIOS.description: UHM club for student interested in the second language studies degrees.

RIOS.name: Shooting Stars
RIOS.description: UHM club students interested in astronomy.

RIOS.name: Silver Wings
RIOS.description: Silver Wings (SW) is a national, professional organization dedicated to creating effective civic leaders through community service and educational workshops. It is a close-knit community that fosters growth and learning, and will hone the skills for you to be ready for professional opportunities after college (whether it be employment, higher education, or even the military). As a member, there are regional and national conclaves one can attend to learn from, and even network with, both military and civilian leaders.

RIOS.name: Smash Bros. Club at The University of Hawaii at Manoa
RIOS.description: Welcome to the UHM Smash Club! This is a club that allows anybody within the UH System Schools to come together and play Smash Bros. Melee, Project M, and Smash 4. This club welcomes both the competitive and non-competitive players, but will be more focused on competitive play. If you are not a competitive smasher, but are interested in becoming one, we will do our best to guide you into the community.

RIOS.name: Society of American Archivists University of Hawai'i Student Chapter
RIOS.description: SAA-SC will provide students with a strong understanding of the world of archives through community service, professional development and contact building.

RIOS.name: Society of Automotive Engineers at UH Manoa
RIOS.description: SAE at University of Hawaii Manoa is a registered independent organization (RIO) and an official collegiate chapter of SAE international. The club is based out of UHM's College of Engineering and offers members the opportunity to get hands on engineering project experience and fabrication method training.

RIOS.name: Society for Human Resource Management, Aloha Chapter
RIOS.description: Welcome to the official page of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM) – Aloha Chapter, founded in 1974. Along with being the student chapter of SHRM Hawaii and an affiliate of SHRM®, the world’s largest association devoted to human resource management, we are dedicated to helping our members achieve new heights by helping them hone their personal and professional skills while creating an empowering environment. We are open to all students and continuously strive for excellence in and out of the classroom.

RIOS.name: Society of Nepalese in Hawaii
RIOS.description: The Society of Nepalese in Hawaii (SNEHA) is a public, non-profit, non-political organization [501 (C) (3)] located in Honolulu, Hawaii. Established in 2007 with the shared faith of “SNEHA” “स्नेह” which means “affection, tenderness, or love”, SNEHA is organized and operated exclusively for charitable purposes and dreams in providing affectionate support to the individuals and societies in need.

RIOS.name: Society of Physics Students at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
RIOS.description: The Society of Physics Students at the University of Hawaii at Manoa (SPS@UHM) aims to foster the physics student community.  Throughout the year, we provide activities that promote the skills necessary for a profession in scientific research. These skills include effective communication and personal interactions, leadership experience, establishing a personal network of contacts, presenting scholarly work in professional meetings and journals, and outreach services to the campus and local communities.

RIOS.name: Society of Women Engineers
RIOS.description: The Society of Women Engineers collegiate section at the University of Hawaii at Manoa is one of the most active engineering societies on campus. Our members include both female and male engineering students who promote women in engineering. Through SWE events, SWE members build community, network with local professional female engineers, demonstrate the value of diversity and expand the image of the engineering profession as a positive force in the quality of life.

RIOS.name: Spanish and Portugese Club
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in Spanish and Portugese.

RIOS.name: Speech Communication Society
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in the speech communication degrees.

RIOS.name: STAR Club
RIOS.description: Assist students to ease the process of earning a degree through technology. Assistance with registration, retention and support.

RIOS.name: Stole Society
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in the stoles of the graduates.

RIOS.name: Students for a National Health Program at University of Hawaii
RIOS.description: Welcome to Students for a National Health Program, the student arm of Physicians for a National Health Program (PNHP). PNHP is a single issue organization advocating a universal, comprehensive single-payer national health program with more than 19,000 members. We believe that a single publicly funded, privately delivered universal health care system is necessary for us to provide high quality care to all our patients.

RIOS.name: Student Immunization Initiative
RIOS.description: Student Immunization Initiative (SII), led by graduate students of the University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa, advocates the importance of immunization. SII has worked with Hawaii Immunization Coalition (HIC) and is currently a member of Hawaii’s Vaccine-Preventable Cancers Workgroup. Educational outreach programs on immunization led by university- or graduate-level students are limited in Hawaii. Because the majority of SII members participate in biomedical research including vaccine development, they have insight on the concepts and benefits of vaccines. Through SII educational events not only will the public benefit from learning about the importance of vaccination and disease prevention, but members will also develop skills in explaining difficult health topics to the community.

RIOS.name: Student Interest Group for Neurology and Psychiatry
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in neurology and psychiatry.

RIOS.name: Students Interested in Pathology
RIOS.description: Students Interested in Pathology (SIP) is the official pathology interest group at the University of Hawai’i, John A. Burns School of Medicine.  SIP members have opportunities to participate in Tumor Boards and observe physicians discussing difficult cases. We offer regularly scheduled activities such as: mystery pathology cases, exam review sessions, and special presentations. Students also learn about autopsy requirements and pathology electives.  SIP members have access to observership/shadowing opportunities, research opportunities, residency Q&A panels, and more!

RIOS.name: Students with Keiki @ the University of Hawaii- Manoa
RIOS.description: Student Parent Club at UH Manoa working to connect parents with resources and support on and off campus.

RIOS.name: Student Nurses' Association
RIOS.description: The Student Nurses’ Association at the University of Hawaii at Manoa (SNA) is the school chapter of the National Student Nurses Association (NSNA) and the Hawaii Student Nurses’ Association (HISNA). The goal of the SNA is to provide students with opportunities to develop leadership skills and enhance their professional nursing identity. Members of this student-led organization participate on school committees and plan various community service, social, and scholarly activities. All activities carried out by the SNA uphold the six core values of the NSNA, which are Leadership and Autonomy, Quality Education, Advocacy, Professionalism, Care, and Diversity.

RIOS.name: Student Veteran Organization
RIOS.description: UHM club for student veterans.

RIOS.name: Supporting Women in Information, Technology and Computing in Hawaii at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
RIOS.description: SWITCH is the culmination of efforts of the awesome students, faculty, and working professionals supporting social change in the ICS department.  Established in Fall 2019, we are officially a UH Manoa RIO, ACM-W Chapter, and Girls Who Code College Loops Chapter. We strive to provide useful resources from these organizations to improve your professional, technical, and personal development.

RIOS.name: Surfrider Foundation UH Manoa Club
RIOS.description: Our mission is the protection and enjoyment of oceans, waves and beaches through a powerful student activist network. Our ocean, waves and beaches belong to all of us and it is our job to protect them.

RIOS.name: Thai Studies Club
RIOS.description: The Thai Studies Club at the University of Hawaii at Manoa seeks to promote a better understanding of Thailand and its people, including language, culture and society.

RIOS.name: The Anime Manga Society of Hawaii at UH Manoa
RIOS.description: We are an open community of people who love to watch Japanese anime, read manga, have an interest in gaming, cosplay, Japanese culture, western comics/animation, or anything related.

RIOS.name: The Elohist Club at UH
RIOS.description: Elohist Club is a group of university student volunteers from the Church of God, who act to solve practical problems around the world. People are suffering from disasters such as earthquakes, volcanic eruptions, terrorist attacks, wars, and climate catastrophes caused by climate change. We were recognized by the state of Hawaii with the "Good Neighbor & Environmental Hero Award" , "Certificate of Appreciation" from the City and County of Honolulu & "Certificate of Appreciation" from the Blood Bank of Hawaii.

RIOS.name: The Engineers' Council at the University of Hawaii
RIOS.description: The Engineer’s Council at the University of Hawaiʻi (ECUH) is a student-operated executive board, consisting of elected executive board (officer) positions, affiliate College of Engineering (COE) student organization representatives, and a general member body. The mission of the ECUH is to provide unity action through cooperative, transparent, and effective representation of the student body of the COE at the University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa. By collaborating with students, faculty, affiliated student organizations, and professional partners, the ECUH serves to promote academic, intellectual, cultural, and social understanding throughout the COE, and to provide students with the finest education environment possible.

RIOS.name: The Ethnomusicology Association
RIOS.description: EMA is the ethnomusicology-focused, student-run organization of the University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa.

RIOS.name: The Healing Earth Initiative
RIOS.description: Current focus is on composting.  They have received funding from ASUH.  Want to start at Paradise Palms, then spread to CC and Bale etc. Want to educate students on the importance of composting. Collaborating with Surfrider and other community organizations.

RIOS.name: The iMua Learned Society at the Univeristy of Hawaii (iMua Living Labs)
RIOS.description: UHM club for student innovation.

RIOS.name: The Language Documentation Training Center
RIOS.description: The Language Documentation Training Center of the Department of Linguistics at the University of Hawai‘i at Mānoa aims to train community members of underdocumented languages in the skills of language documentation, while spreading awareness about linguistic diversity and language endangerment.

RIOS.name: The National Society of Collegiate Scholars, University of Hawai'i at Manoa Chapter
RIOS.description: NSCS at the University of Hawaii at Manoa is an honor society inviting high-achieving freshmen and sophomores. Members must have a GPA of 3.4 or above and rank in the top 20 percent of their class.

RIOS.name: The Navigators
RIOS.description: In 2006, the Navigators leadership made a commitment to start 10 new ministries on ethnically diverse campuses in the United States. University of Hawaii was on the top of that list.

RIOS.name: The Pre-Dental Association at the University of Hawaii at Manoa
RIOS.description: Our goal is to help our fellow members to become competitive dental school applicants by providing a network of resources such as shadowing opportunities, volunteering opportunities, and meeting dental school admissions committee. It is a fantastic opportunity to connect with others who have the same goal and who are also willing to help you reach your goal of becoming a dentist.

RIOS.name: The Students for Success Club
RIOS.description: UHM club for helping students succeed.

RIOS.name: Timpuyog Organization
RIOS.description: Proudly supported by the Ilokano Language Program is the student run organization, Timpuyog, which promotes its cultural and language activities, including the end-of-semester Ilokano drama, sarsuela, video production, and song and dance competition at the University of Hawaii at Manoa, that culminates in a feast of Filipino delicacies. The Timpuyog Organization also occasionally co-sponsors socials and sports events, participated by the students in other clubs, schools, and youth groups in the community.

RIOS.name: Transcendental Meditation Club
RIOS.description: Transcendental Meditation — brought to the West in 1959 by Maharishi Mahesh Yogi — is an ancient technique that's easy to learn and enjoyable to practice. It's not a religion, philosophy, or lifestyle. Over ten million people have learned it — people of all ages, cultures, and religions.

RIOS.name: Travel Industry Management Student Association
RIOS.description: The Travel Industry Management Student Association (TIMSA) at the University of Hawaii at Manoa (UHM) is a club designed for students of all majors who are passionate about the hospitality and travel industries. By creating a distinct network of peers and industry leaders, TIMSA members will be encouraged and driven to pursue their goals and become successful professionals within their careers.

RIOS.name: Tropical Plant and Soil Sciences Graduate Student Organization
RIOS.description: Join the TPSS graduate student organization for graduate bonding, networking, & professional development.

RIOS.name: Ultrasound Interest Group at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in ultrasound at the JABSOM.

RIOS.name: Volunteers for Intercultural and Definitive Adventures
RIOS.description: Volunteers for Intercultural and Definitive Adventures (VIDA) is a non-profit organization that focuses on providing medical, dental, and veterinary healthcare to impoverished communities in Central America. Hawaii's first VIDA chapter was established in 2014 with the University of Hawaii at Manoa, and since then our UHM volunteers have helped 2300+ patients and 800+ animals.

RIOS.name: WADEM SIG at UHM
RIOS.description: The mission of WADEM is the evidence-based improvement, education, and advocacy of emergency and disaster health care and disaster risk reduction.

RIOS.name: Waikiki Acrobatics Troupe
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in the Waikiki Acrobatics Troupe.

RIOS.name: Wesley Foundation @ UH Manoa
RIOS.description: A United Methodist campus ministry located at the University of Hawaii at Manoa

RIOS.name: Wilderness Medicine Hawaii
RIOS.description: UHM club for students interested in wilderness medicine at the JABSOM.

RIOS.name: Women's Interest Group at JABSOM
RIOS.description: UHM club for women at the JABSOM.

RIOS.name: Younglife
RIOS.description: Young Life doesn't start with a program. It starts with adults who are concerned enough about kids to go to them, on their turf and in their culture, building bridges of authentic friendship. These relationships don't happen overnight — they take time, patience, trust and consistency.
